[4] Cholera - Uganda (Arua, Hoima)
Date: Thu 20 Sep 2007
Source: AllAfrica, The Monitor (Kampala) report [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200709191044.html>

An outbreak of cholera in the West Nile district of Nyadri (in Arua) has
killed one person and left 8 others hospitalized.
"Our investigation shows that the outbreak came from the DR Congo [DRC] and
some cases were contracted during a funeral of a person who died of the
disease," Dr Aldo Pariyo, the officer in charge of Maracha Health
sub-district said yesterday, 19 Sep 2007.
He said that 5 of the 8 cases reported at Maracha Health Centre were
Congolese. Olufe and Oleba sub-counties that border the DRC are said to be
the most affected areas.
Meanwhile, reports from Hoima that the district is also worried of a
possible outbreak of the disease, especially in areas around the shores of
Lake Albert. The district director of Health Services, Dr Joseph Ruyonga,
said his office was still verifying information concerning a reported
outbreak. "The Nkondo LCI [local council, smallest administrative unit]
chairperson has reported to my office that the disease has killed 2 of his
residents," Mr Ruyonga told Daily Monitor.
[byline: Warom Felix Okello]
